WEBVTT

00:04:27.626 --> 00:04:30.521
"Holy moly, you vacuum yourself
out of a room every day?

00:04:30.545 --> 00:04:32.396
And you make a scene for the guests

00:04:32.420 --> 00:04:34.534
with the fluffy toys
on the bed every day?"

00:04:34.558 --> 00:04:38.143
Any job done in excellence
is amazing to me.

00:04:41.297 --> 00:04:44.271
AG: Marcus started to recognize
that any job done in excellence

00:04:44.295 --> 00:04:48.658
wasn't because people spent all their time
trying to repair their weaknesses.

00:04:48.682 --> 00:04:52.593
It was usually because someone was working
from a natural or developed strength.

00:04:52.617 --> 00:04:55.873
A strength is more than a skill --
a technical proficiency,

00:04:55.897 --> 00:04:58.908
like working with numbers
or using a certain kind of tool.

00:04:59.752 --> 00:05:03.736
Your strengths are broader aptitudes
you have or build